reviews.text: A nice little beach park you can get a good workout on the sand and rocks. There's a cute little trail off the beaten path like a little forest on the beach. Easy enough for kids. If you go during the off season be aware the lighthouse is only open on weekends. The stairs up to the top of the lighthouse would've been a great workout as well.

My favorite lighthouse in NJ. The park is clean and well maintained, and the bathrooms are fairly well kept for public facilities. Running out of paper towels and soap in the ladies' room at the park entrance, and people leaving messes in the toilets, are the only negative things I have seen. A good place to visit for anyone.
Always try to climb 'Olde Barney' when I come back Long Beach Island. 217 steps up and down in 20+ minutes.  Not bad for an old Lifeguard whose will be 70 on his next Birthday!
Had an awesome time here with my family. The view from on top of the lighthouse was amazing. The all around scenery was really something. Will visit again very soon.

This is a wonderful place to visit. The walk along the water where they have a cement pathway is amazing! We saw a harbor seal resting on the rocks right by the lighthouse and many other wildlife. There is also a trail through the wooded area on the other side of the lighthouse.
Has a great presentation of LBI history and Peg was a great guide that knew all the little details.
A great collection of the islands history in wonderful old building. There is also an excellent little gift shop. Stop by and support what they do.
The cutest little museum

Quaint, attractive museum nestled in the heart of Beach Haven across the street from the old Engleside Hotel's site.  Lots of artifacts and displays regarding the heyday of NJ luxury seaside hotels, local history (including the 1916 Shark Attacks) and plenty of photos and prints.  Near the heart of town but enough off the main drag enough to offer a little solitude.
Great history of LBI

Scojo's is a must-stop whenever I'm in the area. The food is never short of fantastic and the service is amazing. I'm especially fond of their breakfast offerings. The serving sizes are all generous. Call ahead, even during the off-peak season, but any wait you may experience is worthwhile.
The food was amazing ,staff was awesome. I had a Reuben and my kid had a burger. Not a single thing was wrong with this meal it was great.

A good little breakfast place. Nothing particularly special about it, and at the same time no detractors. A good little breakfast place. It's small and fills quickly. Either get there early or be prepared to wait to be seated.
The owners and staff treat you like family! The food is amazing and the atmosphere is so cozy. From breakfast to dinner, it’s always a great meal.
Great spot and food for breakfast, brunch, or lunch. Staff are welcoming and responsive. It's an island favorite place.

Glad to be down in New Jersey again to experience real NY style pizza. This place sits across from the water park and is delicious and only serves pizza or fries from a pickup window and both are excellent!! I ordered a slice here and it was gigantic and so greasy and good I loved it! The fries were equally great, skins on and long and large and tasty. Prices are right and they serve old style sodas from Birch beer to 7up. Loved it!
Best pizza I’ve had down the shore tastes just like a New York style pizza. The mystic iced tea was the best iced tea I’ve ever had. Where can you buy it? Anybody know?
Good pizza, they boast the biggest slice which is basically 2 regular slices. Only problem is it's $22 for a whole pizza. Obviously over the average price but you are at the shore.
Tasted like good pizza and the seasoned fries were savoury. Satisfied albeit the fries a little high in price.
Fantastic pizza and fries! The place to get pizza in Beach Haven.

I came here for sushi and thought the rolls were tiny, mostly rice, and expensive. I also ordered miso soup that tasted mostly of water. I was disappointed in this place and for the price, probably wouldn't return. The service was fine and the view is nice. A man next to me had ordered a burger and onion rings that looked good, so maybe the grill section is better than the sushi...

The servers need to be trained in customer service. One worker was standing on the stairs to the patio while looking down at her phone and blocking the way to downstairs.  A second server was behind me getting chairs to move and lifted them right into the back of my chair.  He could have asked me politely to move so he could get the chairs.  The rudest of them all was some girl who came over and sprayed cleaner on a section of the table while we were still eating and had food out.  Seriously, I don’t want to ingest whatever chemicals were in that bottle. Then she kept staring at our table. The food was subpar and greasy.  I would not go back or recommend this place.
Good but pricey for what you got

Sushi and grill are run separately. 
Sushi was fresh, tasty, and competently made. Rolls were even cut into small pieces to make it easier for children to eat. Quality was higher and price was lower than you would expect for vacation destination.
Grill has a range of traditional options. Portions are generous and prices were reasonable for vacation spot. Fried items tasty. Cheese steak was slightly overdone.

Tasty options! Well prepared and good sized portions. Indoor and Outdoor Seating areas available. Clean environment. A member of our party got the grilled cheese and has raved about it. I got the grilled chicken wrap which was very good as well. The quesadilla had a generous portion of chicken in it. ... We didn't try the sushi but know someone that did and he said it was really good. It looked good from those that ordered it. Fresh. Next time, I'm getting Sushi there.

Amazing food and lots of food for what you pay for. The breaded chicken was delicious and filling they make the sandwiches really well. Absolutely recommend this place for any type of sandwich you are in the mood for.
Friendly staff and good food and sandwiches when we are in LBI.
Alway good food and friendly service.

The building is clearly steeped in the history of the area, and it shows in the wood structure of the interior, as well as the black-and-white pictures hung all around the store. It's really cool! In addition, the store offers an  interesting selection of snacks, some of which I was not expecting (the MANY different varieties of Milano cookies, for example)! The breakfast sandwiches are delicious. I highly recommend stopping by this place for a quick, delicious breakfast!
THE BEST bagels I've ever tasted in my life.

Phenomenal from the appetizer to the main course. Family style restaurant - order it all and fork(sword) fight over the delicious selections. We had a little bit of everything and was not disappointed. Very attentive staff. Popular place in town will get full so plan accordingly!

Our dinner was great! The six of us all loved our food, shares, sides.  Sunset was lovely and one of few places you can see it.  Only downside is making reservations is difficult.  No one ever answers the phone & the app declines all reservations for 6 or more,  makes you go to waiting list then approves you later when it was always available. I'm sure they are losing business due to lack of human answering.

What a terrific restaurant. My party of three tried appetizers,  a different entree each and then, because everyone raved about the appetizers and entrees,  we ordered a dessert that was large enough to split three ways. We rarely order dessert. This is a BYOB place and had we known,  would have brought a bottle of wine. Don't miss this place.

Great ambience, wonderful service, but some of our food literally was inedible- loaded with salt!  And this is from someone who loves potato chips.  We could not eat our flounder because it was so salty.  We sent it back and lo and behold - we got the same fish back again, as salty as ever, and recooked - the edges were browned.  We had no choice but to send it back again - really irritated this time.  We overhead a person at the next table commenting on his fish being too salty.   And the calamari was full of salt, too.
There was something wrong in this kitchen in mid-August.  And I wouldn't recommend the place  - they just didn't rectify the situation promptly and correctly.

Great food and atmosphere.  Attentive wait staff.  Watch out for added charges.  We had 4 people and ordered 3 appetizers and 4 dinners.  We were charged $2 each for shared plates for the appetizers.  In addition, we brought a birthday cake and were charged another $2 each  cake plates.  Total charge for 8 plates was $16.

The 5 stars are because of the great food...not the atmosphere or the service. The fried lobster is wonderful. I got 5 pieces of lobster that looked to be tail halves. Good bread, adequate salad. Wife got seafood combo, also very good, loved the crab cake. A nice option other than potatoes was asparagus with no up charge. The asparagus was fresh, nicely done, not overcooked. Rolls also good.   Service is adequate, a little slow but that might have been the kitchen getting behind.

They do not take reservations. We got there (Saturday night) around 6:45 and had a little more than a half hour wait. You can look at the boats at the marina! Near the end of our wait they were telling new comers 1 1/2 hours. This place is LOUD.  Not cozy, quiet, and romantic. It is neat and clean, but loud. It seems to be mostly locals dining here. It is BYOB and lots of people do just that. Don't think there is a corking fee as most of what I saw was people opening their own bottles (except for some that forgot the corkscrew LOL). This place is well rehearsed at turning over tables. We were watching this one young woman. A table of six left, and within 3.5 minutes she had QUIETLY cleared the table and reset it for six again. We were timing her for fun, and she was consistent and fun to watch.  Dessert options were not impressive, in fact, the dessert menu was exactly the same as where we ate last night...this area needs improvement. We did not order dessert. Pictured is the lobster and the combo. (Lemons already removed from the one plate...they are generous with the lemons too)

Food was decent. Service was just ok. I know our server had other tables some larger than ours but waited 15 minutes for the check after it was asked for then another 15-20 minutes for server to come back and run card. Pretty much 35 to 40 minutes waiting to pay. It was getting to the point where it was about to become a dine and dash. Just didn't have it in me to do it.

One of the best restaurants that I’ve been to in a long time. Great service. Menu had a lot of options. Prices are normal seafood prices. I highly suggest the miso salmon. It was cooked perfectly. Nice crust on top. Super tender inside. Great flavor. This is one of the few meals I’ve had pretty much no complaints about and we were happy the whole time. It also overlooks a marina and has a parking lot. Totally awesome, high quality place that takes pride in their food. They don’t blast music either. It’s highly recommended.
Wonderful experience every time. Great food, great service. Best lobster bisque! Worth every calorie! 😂
Both food and service were excellent.  Byob is convenient.  Can tell why they have stayed in business as long as they have with so much of the island changing. Will definitely be returning.

Good food. Ordered fries and when I got them was only enough for one person (in my opinion). Maybe I should have asked for a large serving for 5 people but I would have expected them to ask what size I wanted. Most other pizza joints give a healthy size serving if just ordering one. This place not so much if not told. Otherwise nice place to eat.
Really good pizza. The CHOWDER is AWESOME! In a toasted bread bowl is the best treat ever.
Casual dinning restaurant. They have some really good pizza and in the summer have late night hours.
Always great food and great service. Best New England clam chowder!

This place has decent food. It's really good variety. Prices are not economical by any means but you're on Long Beach Island nothing is cheap. As far as LBI goes the prices are about average. The food is certainly decent. Service is pretty quick. And the staff is friendly.

The New Year’s Eve “special menu” was doubled in price & very limited. You had to buy a package which included an appetizer & dessert. My appetizer of fresh tuna was  paltry and served on 2 tortilla chips .It was tasty,but  looked like elf food. My companion’ s meal was a chicken & veal combo covered in brown gravy.It looked like a giant burger. Not a piece of parsley or vegetable in sight to improve an unappetizing presentation.  Our meals were not special at all and very over priced.
Absolutely fantastic food. Service could be a little better, but I've never had a bad experience at Roberto's.
Excellent meal! Calamari was cooked perfectly, sauce homemade. Veal Pizzaiola nicely spiced, excellent sauce. Old fashioned Veal Parmigiana also great. We are going again for sure
Really good food and professional and courteous staff. We enjoyed our time.  Its BYOB but they charge if you bring a cake to cut
restaurant was cold,  food was okay,  service was good
Endless Paella. Excellent. Best Restaurant on the Island
If you're on the North side of LBI, it's the best place to eat.

Excellent food, excellent atmosphere, excellent service. I've been there quite a few times. Only one suggestion,  the menu needs to be expanded. It always seems to be the same, other than that it's a must go to place....
One of the best seafood restaurants that I have ever eaten in and also top notch service it's a must to eat there
Food was great, also great service and staff.
